I just had the worst experience even entering this place. I was asked by a 40+ man if I needed help and I said, “yes, do you have gelato or you only carry ice-cream? (I googled gelato places in Bay Ridge & it was the closest option for me) He replied rudely while looking me up and down “In case you didn’t know, ice-cream and gelato are the same thing.” I was born and raised in Italy and obviously know the difference between the two, so I said “Actually, they’re not.” “What’s the difference then?” He asked immediately. I replied “Ice cream is made with milk and gelato is made with heavy cream.” His reply: “so ice-cream is healthier! we have ice-cream.” He didn’t even wait to look at my reaction and walked away. In shock, I said “thank you” and walked out. What happened to customer service? What happened to respect? I am a 100lb 5’1” mom of two daughters, not intimidating at all, nor was I rude. I’m appalled to be treated like that! In a time in which restaurants struggle, the last thing you need to do is turn away customers by putting them down. Not acceptable, not ok, never again. I’ll make sure to tell all my neighbors to NOT support you.

You guys have to get a little more creative. We opted out of eating there today and are across the street at Foundry.  As they are good to I would have much rather had breakfast at Anopoli.  Can’t wait till things go back to normal!  Be well

1-HOUR long wait for two eggs each. Review Yelp: Jess, Hannah, Rob, John, Doug, Vanessa, the list goes on, ref: OWNER.  DINE AT YOUR OWN RISK. Excellent female staff of ladies--with the exception of the one tall/dark haired male. Completely unprofessional and rude beyond belief. We exercised extreme patience/did not make any mention to our server Megan until 40 min. after ordering. She was polite/apologetic/friendly. This male "server" took it upon himself to approach us--couple of minutes after finally being served 1-hour after--to start an argument with us, on Mother's Day. My mother is 80 years old and needs to eat with her medication. Unbelievably ignorant and unprofessional individual.  After repeatedly/politely and eventually assertively requesting him to please not approach us, it literally ended in him aimlessly stomping around the restaurant, completely unable to hold himself together--and emotionally beginning a literal shouting match for the last word with a paying customer--who, already in the wrong, waited 1 hour for food--to be played out in front of the entire restaurant. If you do not know how to communicate in customer service + fail (please read reviews) to exercise the basic skill set of patience--you should not be trying to talk to paying customers. This is not an isolated incident with him from myself or neighbors.  In the end the wait is bad but irrelevant. The affable/apologetic kitchen + floor staff who apologized with dignity to us could not make up for the outrageous disservice from him. We all work. No job exist without stress. Welcome to work. Disgusting display of unprofessionalism at the job site.  His mantra: when the restaurant is wrong, the customer waits 1 hour..is wrong..gets bullied..yelled at.  Thank god I do not put up with this.  One of a couple of more diners on 3rd (our family owned a restaurant in BK '50-60's so I support family business) & good female staff. One star for them only as a neighbor from 72nd Street.
